#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:350 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1918
#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1948
msgid "Movement Guidelines"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:352
msgid "DMs always move towards the"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:353
msgid ""
"closest player Colony. If two Colonies are equidistant, then a DM will "
"always move toward the Colony that is larger (in CP). If more than one "
"equidistant Colonies are the same size, then the DM will move towards the"
" Colony that brings it closest to the player’s Homeworld. If it is still "
"tied, then it is the player’s choice. As a DM moves toward a Colony, if "
"two different hexes will put it equidistant from the target Colony, it "
"will move toward the hex that is also closer to the player’s Homeworld. "
"Each time a DM moves, its target Colony may change. The player may not "
"reduce a Colony or remove it in order to change the direction of a DM."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:361 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3190
msgid "Strength and Weaknesses"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:363
msgid "Each map contains a table"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:364
msgid ""
