msgid ""
"Unlike multiplayer games, DMs do not destroy Asteroids in solitaire "
"scenarios (MRB 29.4)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:411 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3276
msgid "Planets and Colonies"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:413
msgid "If a DM is in a hex with a planet"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:414
msgid ""
"(with or without a Colony), it will destroy that planet. Remove the "
"planet and any Colony from play. The DM must first defeat any defending "
"ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:422
msgid "Doomsday Machine Combat Rules"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:424
msgid ""
"• If a DM moves into a hex with the player’s ships, it will engage them "
"in combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:425
msgid ""
"• Unless specified as a weakness, all DMs are immune to Mines, Fighters "
"(their weaponry is too small to affect them), and Cloaking (they are "
"equipped with the highest level of Scanners)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:426
msgid ""
"• The player does not get the Fleet Size Bonus (MRB 5.1.3) for "
"outnumbering a DM."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:427
msgid ""
"• A roll of 1 is not an automatic hit on a DM. However, a roll of 1 by a "
"DM is always a hit. A DM that rolls a 10 is always a miss."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:428
msgid ""
"• DMs carry damage from combat to combat (they do not automatically "
"heal). However, they do heal two damage instantly every time they destroy"
" a planet (whether or not it has a Colony)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:429
msgid ""
"• DMs get more than one attack per round as shown on the table (2.5). All"
" attacks are of the same strength and occur at the same time. A DM is "
"considered to have Tactics 2."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:430
msgid ""
"• The player should use common sense when allocating the attacks of a DM."
" If weak against Fighters, it should target Fighters. If weak against "
"large fleets, it should attack smaller ships or damaged ships in order to"
" get the fleet size under 10, etc. Like with human players, DMs may roll "
"their attacks one at a time and see the result before rolling more "
"attacks."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:431
msgid "• A DM never retreats from combat."
msgstr ""

