"may not be used. The Alien Players do not use any new ships/technologies "
"from the Replicators expansion."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1600 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3342
msgid "Black Hole Jumping"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1602
msgid "At the start of the game, there are"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1603
msgid ""
"two Warp Points beside the player’s Home System that connect to a Warp "
"Point located at the Galactic Capitol. This is how the player discovered "
"and developed a relationship with the Galactic Capitol. The Galactic "
"Capitol has provided the plans for a new technology to the player called "
"Black Hole Jumping."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1604 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1610
msgid ""
"• This technology has 2 levels costing 20 CP (level 1) and 40 CP (level "
"2)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1605
msgid "• If researched, it should be noted on the player’s Production Sheet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1606
msgid ""
"• On Hard difficulty, Movement 3 must be researched before the player can"
" gain this technology."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1607 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1611
msgid ""
"• All ships may be equipped with Black Hole Jumping technology as if it "
"were a kind of Movement technology. Level 1 enables these ships to freely"
" enter a Black Hole without having to roll for survival. At Level 2, "
"those ships may treat all faceup Black Holes and Warp Points on the map "
"as being connected. They may “jump” through them as if those hexes were "
"adjacent, as per the normal Warp Point rules (MRB 28.2)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1619
msgid "Alien Starting Technology"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1621
msgid "All APs start the game with"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1622
msgid "Terraforming 1, Exploration 1, and Ground Combat 1 technologies."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1630
msgid "Alien Colonies"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1632
msgid "The Alien Players can capture or build"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1633
msgid ""
"Colonies, just like the human player. Doing so gives them a boost to "
"their economy and helps them win the game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1641
msgid "Attacking Alien Colonies"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1643
msgid "The player may attack Colonies"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1644
msgid ""
"(MRB 5.10) owned by an AP to damage that AP’s economy, and they may also "
"capture those Colonies with Ground Units. If an AP Colony is destroyed or"
" captured, subtract 2 VPs from their Victory Point Track and subtract one"
" from the “# Colonies” column of that AP’s “Alien Economic Sheet – "
"Victory Track Scenarios” found on page 53. The Victory Point Track may go"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1645
msgid "Space Empires: All Good Things - Solo/Coop Scenario Book Version 1.0 17"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1646
msgid ""
"below zero. If below zero, track the value as negative marking the "
"Victory Point counter with a spare damage counter. If an AP Colony was "
"previously owned by the player, it must be recaptured with Ground Units "
"to liberate the Colony; the player may not eliminate the Colony by "
"bombardment. Those are your people down there!"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1654
msgid "APs Gaining Alien Technology Cards"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1656
msgid "If an AP captures"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1657
msgid ""
"an NPA planet (MRB 18.0), the APs draw an Alien Technology card (MRB "
"11.0). They may not use the card’s effects; however, drawing an Alien "
"Technology card gives the Alien Players VPs. Every Alien Technology card "
"in the APs’ possession give them +1 VP. This is in addition to VPs that "
"the AP may have gained by taking Colonies."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1665
msgid "Stealing Alien Technology Cards"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1667
msgid "If the human player"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1668
msgid ""
"uses Ground Units to capture an AP Colony in Deep Space, they may steal "
"(at random) one of the Alien Technology cards the APs have earned. The "
"player does not get to do this if they colonize a planet previously owned"
" by an AP; in other words, a player cannot destroy an AP Colony by "
"bombardment and then gain an Alien Technology card by recolonizing that "
"same planet. Once taken by the player, these cards may be used as normal."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1669
msgid ""
"The player does not get to take an Alien Technology card from the AP when"
" recapturing a Colony that used to be their own."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1670
msgid ""
"If the APs use Ground Units to capture a player-owned Deep Space Colony, "
"they do not steal an Alien Technology card from the player, and they do "
"not otherwise gain a card for that planet’s capture. An AP can never "
"steal an Alien Technology card from a human player."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1678
msgid "Capturing Alien Player Technology"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1680
msgid "The player may"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1681
msgid ""
"gain technology from an AP by capturing their Colonies (MRB 21.13.6). All"
" AP Colonies are treated as Deep Space Colonies, so only one level of one"
" technology may be gained."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1689
msgid "Eliminating AP Homeworlds"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1691
msgid "In scenarios with more than"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1692
msgid ""
"one AP opponent, an eliminated AP may continue acting. If an AP Homeworld"
" is eliminated, the AP’s units (including those not yet revealed) are not"
" removed from the game board. Any currently active fleets continue acting"
" as normal. This AP can no longer gain VP or Alien Technology cards by "
"the action of its remaining fleets but can still potentially cause the "
"player to lose the game. Elimination of this AP’s remaining Colonies "
"still reduces the Alien Players’ VPs on the Victory Point Track as "
"normal."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1702
msgid ""
"See the “Alien Economic Sheet – Victory Track Scenarios” on page 53 and "
"the flowcharts on pages 57-61 to see how the Alien Players generate CP, "
"launch fleets, buy tech, and buy ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1710
msgid "Types of Alien Fleets"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1712
msgid "When an AP launches a fleet from"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1713
msgid ""
"their Homeworld, it will be either an Extermination fleet (6.6), an "
"Expansion fleet (6.7), or a Raider fleet (6.9). Extermination fleets try "
"to destroy or capture the player’s Homeworld or the Galactic Capitol. "
"Expansion fleets target the nearest Colony or Non-Player Alien planet for"
" capture or colonization. Raider"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1714 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1717
msgid ""
"fleets always target the nearest, least defended player Colony. If 3 "
"fleets are already in play for this AP, launch is cancelled."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1725
msgid "Bank and Defense Limits"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1727
msgid "If an AP launches an"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1728
msgid ""
"Expansion fleet (6.7) it will add 50 CP to that fleet from the Bank, if "
"able. An AP may never gain more than 50 CP in the Defense column; CP "
"allocated to Defense are first doubled, up to the maximum, and then any "
"remainder is allocated to the Bank. An AP will reroll any Defense result "
"(until it gets a different result) on an Economic Roll (4.2) if it "
"already has 50 CP in its Defense column."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1736
msgid "Economic Phase"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1738
msgid "Alien Player Economic Phases are"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1739
msgid "performed after the player has completed their own."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1747
msgid "Shared Intelligence"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1749
msgid "The APs share all information as"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1750
msgid "far as seeing the human player’s technology, ship types, and experience."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1758
msgid "Resource Gathering"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1760 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1764
msgid "If an Extermination fleet or an"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1761 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1765
msgid ""
"Expansion fleet is colocated with a Mineral after resolving any space "
"combat, set the Mineral aside. Doing so gives the APs 1 extra temporary "
"Econ Roll in the next Econ Phase. Set the mineral on the next Econ Phase "
"column of the AP production sheet to denote this and then remove it from "
"the game once the extra roll has been used in the next Econ Phase. Raider"
" fleets may not collect Minerals."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1773 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:3265
msgid "Space Wrecks"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1775
msgid "If any AP fleet moves onto a Space Wreck"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1776
msgid "(MRB 6.8), the Space Wreck is destroyed immediately. No VPs are earned."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1784 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2618
msgid "Colonization"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1786
msgid "If an AP fleet moves onto a planet (either an"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1787
msgid ""
"NPA planet, Player Colony, Player Homeworld, or the Galactic Capitol), "
"there is a chance they will either build Ground Units to invade the "
"planet or build a Colony Ship after destroying the ships in orbit in "
"order to colonize the planet (6.8.4). Capturing or colonizing a planet "
"does not generate 1-5 CP per Economic Phase as it does for a human "
"player, though AP Colonies grow each Economic Phase as usual. Instead, "
"during the AP’s Economic Phase, they roll 1 extra Econ Roll for every "
"Colony that AP owns which would normally produce income (i.e., is at "
"least a “1” Colony and is not blockaded.) An AP Colony does not provide "
"the AP with an extra Econ Roll if it is blockaded."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1795
msgid "Blockaded AP Homeworlds"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1797
msgid "If an AP Homeworld"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1798
msgid ""
"is blockaded it will continue to resolve Economic Phases as normal, "
"except it will no longer launch fleets and all CP will go into their "
"Defense column up to the Defense limit; any overflow will go into the "
"Bank. On the AP’s next Movement Phase, it will launch a Defense fleet "
"(see Defense flowchart) that will immediately engage any fleet blockading"
" their Homeworld."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1806
msgid "Combat Priorities"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1808
msgid "An Alien Player never retreats from"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1809
msgid ""
"battle, will position defensively if out of range of its target Colony, "
"and will attack undefended non-combat ships if it does not alter their "
"time to destination."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1817 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2860
msgid "Screening"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1819
msgid "An Alien Player will screen its own ships,"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1820
msgid "where appropriate, as a human player would."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1821
msgid "Space Empires: All Good Things - Solo/Coop Scenario Book Version 1.0 18"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1829
msgid "Captured Ships"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1831
msgid "Ships captured by AP Boarding Ships"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1832
msgid ""
"may not be scrapped for technology (MRB 19.5); the AP will just use "
"captured ships in battle."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1840
msgid "Capturing Player Technology"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1842
msgid "If an AP uses Ground"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1843
msgid ""
"Units to capture a Colony that is owned by the human player, the AP gains"
" technology as if they were a human player in a competitive game (MRB "
"21.13). For the capture of a Home System Colony, the AP gains one level "
"of up to two technologies that they can purchase in which the human "
"player is more advanced. For the capture of a Deep Space Colony, the AP "
"gains one level of technology that they can purchase in which the human "
"player is more advanced. In either case, the AP also gains 10 CP in its "
"Tech column and counts as having encountered any technology that the "
"human player has researched when it makes future purchase decisions."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1851
msgid "Experience Levels"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1853
msgid "Use a normal ship tracking sheet to"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1854
msgid ""
"track AP ship experience levels (MRB 37.0). AP ships may gain experience "
"from destroying NPA and player ships as normal. All ships in an "
"unrevealed AP fleet should be treated as normal in terms of promotion "
"from Green experience level and use of Military Academy when they are "
"ultimately revealed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1862
msgid "Minesweepers"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1864
msgid "Alien Player Scouts can equip"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1865
msgid "Minesweeper technology (MRB 17.0). Minesweeper ships are not used by APs."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1873
msgid "Regional Map and Space Pirates have no effect on AP"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1875 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1878
msgid "if revealed. Just discard them if revealed by the AP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1886
msgid "The AP will attempt to avoid Cosmic Storm hexes if"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1888 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1891
msgid "possible. The AP can move through Fold in Space as would a player."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1899 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4326
msgid "Extermination Fleets"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1907 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1937
msgid "Targeting"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1909
msgid "When launched, choose randomly to"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1910
msgid ""
"determine whether an Extermination fleet will target the player’s "
"Homeworld or the Galactic Capitol."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1920
msgid "Extermination fleets make a"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1921
msgid ""
"beeline for their destinations, avoiding combat with the player and "
"avoiding other Colonies, if able. However, the fleet will only alter its "
"course to avoid these things if it can still get to its target in the "
"same number of Economic Phases."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1929 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4304
msgid "Expansion Fleets"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1939
msgid "Expansion fleets will always move towards"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1940
msgid ""
"the closest Non-Player Alien planet or player Colony. Closest is defined "
"as the target that can be reached in the fewest number of Economic "
"Phases. If two or more possible destinations are equidistant, the AP "
"chooses the one which will enable it to explore more Deep Spaces hexes."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1950
msgid "An Expansion fleet always moves"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1951
msgid ""
"in the direction of its target, avoiding entering a Homeworld or the "
"Galactic Capitol. Fleet destinations are always reset at the start of "
"each Movement Phase – if the destination becomes"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1952
msgid ""
"friendly (i.e., owned by another AP), then that Expansion fleet will "
"select a new destination. If an Expansion fleet takes a Colony or Non-"
"Player Alien planet the remainder of the fleet, including Ground Units, "
"stays and defends the planet for the rest of the game. This stationary "
"defense fleet no longer counts for this AP’s 3 fleet limit."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1962
msgid "and Exploration"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1963
msgid "The following rules apply to all Extermination and Expansion fleets."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1971
msgid "Movement"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1973
msgid "Extermination and Expansion fleets are hindered"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1974
msgid "by terrain like Asteroids and Nebulae just like human fleets."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1982
msgid "Exploration Technology"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1984
msgid "Extermination and Expansion"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1985
msgid ""
"fleets always have the equivalent of one Cruiser with Exploration 1 "
"technology (regardless of whether a CA is actually in that fleet.) Before"
" moving, the AP flips and reveals one Deep Space marker (per fleet) that "
"is in the direction of the fleet’s destination. They will never enter a "
"Black Hole or an unexplored hex. They cannot scan Deep Space hexes that "
"are not along the fleet’s path. Since they only have the equivalent of "
"one Cruiser, each fleet may only explore one hex per turn like a normal "
"Cruiser."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1993
msgid "Barren Planets"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1995
msgid "If the fleet moves onto a Deep Space"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:1996
msgid ""
"Barren Planet, place four random Non-Player Alien counters there. Combat "
"occurs as if the NPAs were human players. There is a chance during ship "
"buying that the AP will buy Ground Units which will invade as normal. "
"Ground Combat occurs as it would for a normal player invading an NPA "
"planet (MRB 21.12)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2004
msgid "Colonizing Conquered Planets"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2006
msgid "If Ground Combat does"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2007
msgid ""
"not occur (or was unsuccessful) but the Alien Players “won” space combat,"
" a Colony Ship and 2d10 CP worth of escort ships (minimum one Scout) are "
"immediately placed on the corresponding AP’s nearest Colony or Homeworld "
"at no cost to the AP. The escort ships are selected to maximize the "
"number of ships in this fleet. (For example: a roll of 17 CP would yield "
"one Destroyer and one Scout, while a roll of 18 CP would yield three "
"Scouts.) This fleet takes the fastest and safest route possible to the "
"newly conquered planet. This escort fleet does not count for this AP’s 3 "
"fleet limit. The AP ships that conquered the planet remain in orbit to "
"defend it indefinitely as do the escort ships after they have arrived. "
"Planetary bombardment is performed as needed for colonization."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2008
msgid ""
"If this escort fleet’s destination becomes owned by the human player or "
"another AP, it does not change course; this may result in its destruction"
" upon arrival."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2009
msgid ""
"If the Colony Ship and its escorts are destroyed prior to arrival, "
"another Colony Ship and escort fleet are generated using the same method "
"as above at the nearest Colony or Homeworld. If the target planet becomes"
" occupied by another empire, the Colony Ship’s AP will stop generating "
"Colony Ships and escorts."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2010
msgid "Space Empires: All Good Things - Solo/Coop Scenario Book Version 1.0 19"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2018
msgid "Raider Fleets"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2020
msgid ""
"As in the base game, the AP may launch a Raider fleet instead of a normal"
" fleet. These fleets always target the nearest, least defended player "
"Colony. The following rules apply to all Raider fleets."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2028
msgid "Non-Player Aliens"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2030
msgid "Raider fleets will remain cloaked when"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2031
msgid "in the same hex as an NPA planet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2039
msgid "May Not Capture Colonies"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2041
msgid "Unlike Expansion and"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2042
msgid ""
"Extermination fleets, Raider fleets have no chance of building Ground "
"Units to capture a Colony. They may still destroy a Colony and trigger "
"the construction of a Colony Ship (6.8.4)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2052
msgid "Unlike Expansion and Extermination"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2053
msgid ""
"fleets, Raider fleets are unaffected by unrevealed Deep Space markers and"
" do not cause them to become flipped. A player may not enter a hex with "
"an unrevealed Deep Space marker that is occupied by a Raider fleet (the "
"player should have explored it before the Raiders got there). A player "
"may not use Exploration technology on an unrevealed Deep Space marker "
"that is in the same hex as a Raider fleet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2061
msgid "Asteroids and Nebulae"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2063
msgid "Raider fleets are affected by these"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2064
msgid ""
"terrain types just like human fleets. They will avoid Nebulae if able as "
"long as doing so does not change the number of Economic Phases it takes "
"to reach their destination."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2072
msgid "Avoiding Combat"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2074
msgid "Raiders will avoid combat with player"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2075
msgid ""
"fleets if the player fleet has greater CP than the Raider fleet. They "
"also avoid combat with a fleet containing a Flagship if the rest of the "
"Flagship’s fleet CP cost is greater than half the Raider fleet’s CP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2083
msgid "Replicator Solitaire"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2085
msgid ""
"This solitaire scenario against the Replicators includes several "
"flowcharts for reference on pages 62-67."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2093
msgid "Map Setup"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2095
msgid "• Use either the Normal (7.13) or Large (7.14) Replicator Solitaire map."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2096
msgid ""
"• Place each Homeworld anywhere in the Home System row furthest from the "
"opponent."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2104
msgid "Starting Forces & Technology"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2112
msgid "Human Player"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2114
msgid "• 30 CP Homeworld"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2115
msgid "• 4 Colony Ships"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2116
msgid "• 4 Shipyards"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2117
msgid "• 3 Scouts"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2118
msgid "• 1 Miner"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2119 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2131
msgid "• 1 Flagship (optional)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2127
msgid "Replicators"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2129
msgid "• Full Homeworld"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2130
msgid "• 6 Type 0 ships"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2132
msgid "• Point Defense"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2133
msgid "• Scanners"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2134
msgid "• Minesweepers"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2135
msgid ""
"• Move 2 (Move 3 when using <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Fast "
"Replicators #60</span> advantage)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2151
msgid "Difficulty Level"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2153
msgid "• Easy: The player starts with two additional Colony Ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2154
msgid "• Normal: No changes."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2155
msgid ""
"• Hard: Replicators start with two additional Hull Points and one free RP"
" (MRB 40.0). Mark off the first RP box on the Production Sheet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2156
msgid ""
"• Impossible: Replicators start with three additional Hull Points and two"
" free RPs (MRB 40.0). Mark off the first two RP boxes on the Production "
"Sheet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2164
msgid "Hulls (Hull Size/Hull Points)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2166
msgid "See [MRB 40.0] for an"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2167
msgid ""
"explanation of Replicator Hulls. In short, when required to compare the "
"number of Hulls, the terms “Hull Size” and “Hull Points” are equivalent."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2168
msgid ""
"Example: A CA or a Type V ship each count as 2 Hulls. A BB or a Type XIII"
" ship each count as 3 Hulls."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2176
msgid "Excluded Rules"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2178
msgid "The rules listed below are not used in"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2179
msgid ""
"this scenario (*indicated rules are never used in any Replicators "
"scenario)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2180
msgid "• *Facilities (MRB 36.0)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2181
msgid "• *Terraforming 2 (MRB 34.0)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2182
msgid "• *Unique Ships (MRB 40.0)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2183
msgid "• *Experience (MRB 37.0)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2184
msgid "• *Reaction Movement (MRB 35.0)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2185
msgid "• *Space Amoebas (3.0)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2186
msgid "• *Blood Brothers alliances (CSB 1.3.2)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2187
msgid "• Decoys (MRB 8.3)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2188
msgid "• Resource Cards (MRB 39.0)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2189
msgid "• *Galactic Capitol (MRB 28.1)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2190
msgid "• Regional Maps (MRB 25.6)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2191
msgid "Space Empires: All Good Things - Solo/Coop Scenario Book Version 1.0 20"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2192
msgid "• Space Pirates (MRB 25.7)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2193
msgid "• Warp Points (MRB 28.2)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2194
msgid "• Doomsday Machines (MRB 29.0)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2202
msgid "Non-Player Aliens and Alien Technologies"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2204
msgid "Barren"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2205
msgid ""
"Planets in Deep Space are populated by Non-Player Aliens (MRB 18.0). "
"Remove the <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Minesweep Jammer #24</span> "
"card from the Alien Technology deck."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2215
msgid "If playing with Empire Advantages,"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2216
msgid ""
"remove the <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Warp Gates #63</span> "
"Replicator Empire Advantage card from the deck. Deal two facedown Empire "
"Advantage cards and one facedown Replicator Advantage card. After "
"selecting an Empire Advantage for the player, reveal the Replicator "
"Advantage."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2224
msgid "Initiative"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2226
msgid "The Replicators always have Initiative unless"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2227
msgid ""
"the human player spends 15 CP during an Economic Phase. The Replicators "
"never spend CP on Initiative."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2228
msgid ""
"If the human player spends 15 CP to become the first player, they will "
"move first during each turn until the next Economic Phase. If they do not"
" spend 15 CP again, Initiative reverts back to the Replicators. If that "
"happens, the player may spend 15 CP during a later Economic Phase to gain"
" it again."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2236
msgid "Replicator Ship Behavior"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2238
msgid ""
"• When facedown, Replicator ship counters represent Hulls and are not "
"assigned actual ship types until revealed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2239
msgid ""
"• For simplicity, facedown Hulls will be referred to as ships in these "
"rules unless it is necessary to distinguish between the two."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2240
msgid ""
"• The Replicator Flagship and Exploration ships are always faceup and "
"will never colonize planets. All other Replicator ships are facedown "
"until revealed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2241
msgid ""
"• The Replicator Flagship joins Fleets (7.7) and follows the same "
"movement priorities followed by other Replicator ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2242
msgid ""
"• When faceup Replicator ships (except the Flagship and Exploration "
"ships) enter a hex containing a Replicator Colony, they convert back to "
"Hulls representing no specific ship type; remove all but one ship counter"
" of any type and flip it facedown. Then place one or more numeral markers"
" under the ship counter to represent the number of Hulls present."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2243
msgid ""
"Example 1: A facedown Replicator ship counter has a “4” numeral marker "
"under it, representing 4 Hulls. When revealed, the 4 Hulls could become "
"four Type II ships, two Type V ships, etc. Replicator ship types are "
"determined only when such Hulls are revealed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2244
msgid ""
"Example 2: After combat, two Type V ships and two Type II ships (totaling"
" 6 Hulls) occupy a hex with a player Colony. The Replicators bombard and "
"destroy the Colony, after which one Type II ship immediately colonizes "
"the planet (expending 1 Hull). The remaining ships are now in a hex with "
"a Replicator Colony, so they convert to 5 Hulls and are replaced with one"
" ship counter flipped facedown with a “5” numeral marker beneath it."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2252
msgid "Miscellaneous"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2254
msgid ""
"• No information is hidden. Player ships are always faceup and the "
"player’s available technologies are always known to the Replicators for "
"decision-making purposes. However, the Replicators do not get RPs for "
"player technologies until they encounter them in battle."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2255
msgid ""
"• When the rules are not clear on what the Replicators should do or "
"several possible choices are equally valid, roll a die to decide "
"randomly."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2263
msgid "Exploration Procedures"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2265
msgid ""
"During the Economic Phase after the turn in which the Replicator Home "
"System has been fully explored, the Replicators receive:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2266
msgid ""
"• Exploration technology (MRB 9.8) at no cost (check the box on the "
"Production Sheet)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2267
msgid "• Three Exploration ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2268
msgid ""
"Place one Exploration ship each at the three Full Colonies closest to "
"unexplored Deep Space hexes. Those Colonies produce these Exploration "
"ships instead of a Hull during this Econ Phase. If there is a tie for "
"which Colonies are closest, place the Exploration ship at the Full Colony"
" closest to a Deep Space hex that is farthest from the Replicator "
"Homeworld."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2269
msgid ""
"If an Exploration ship must be placed at the Replicator Homeworld, it "
"counts as only one Hull produced. Extra Hulls gained at the Homeworld via"
" spending or Empire Advantage are not used on the Exploration ship."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2270
msgid "No Replicator ship of any kind ever enters an unexplored Deep Space hex."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2271
msgid ""
"Exploration ships only explore by using Exploration technology (MRB 9.8) "
"and never by entering an unexplored System hex."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2272
msgid ""
"When an Exploration ship explores a hex, flip its System marker faceup. "
"The Exploration ship will then enter the hex unless it contains any of "
"the following:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2273
msgid "• Planet with Non-Player Alien ships"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2274
msgid "• Black Hole"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2275
msgid "• Supernova"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2276
msgid "• Fold in Space"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2284
msgid "Flagship Exploration"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2286
msgid "The Replicator Flagship does not"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2287
msgid "equip Exploration technology – even when it is available."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2288
msgid ""
"The Replicator Flagship explores the Replicator Home System like other "
"ships but does not colonize. If the Flagship discovers a Replicator Home "
"System planet, the nearest Replicator ship will prioritize the "
"colonization of that planet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2289
msgid "Space Empires: All Good Things - Solo/Coop Scenario Book Version 1.0 21"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2297
msgid "Exploration Ships"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2299
msgid ""
"Exploration ships do not follow the same movement or priority rules as "
"other ships. One Exploration ship explores directly toward the human "
"player Home System while the other two systematically explore Deep Space "
"in the vicinity of the Replicator Home System."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2307
msgid "Exploring Toward the Human Player"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2309
msgid "The first"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2310
msgid ""
"Exploration ship that moves into Deep Space is designated to create a "
"direct, fully explored path to the human player Home System. After the "
"path is created, this Exploration ship continues exploring to widen that "
"path."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2311
msgid ""
"If two or more Exploration ships enter the first row of Deep Space during"
" the same Movement Phase, the ship closest to the center of the map is "
"designated to explore toward the human player System."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2319
msgid "Exploring Nearby Deep Space"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2321
msgid "The two Exploration ships"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2322
msgid ""
"that are not pathfinding towards the human player are designated to "
"explore, row by row, the Deep Space hexes closest to the Replicator Home "
"System. After the closest row of Deep Space hexes is fully explored the "
"ships explore the next row, and so on."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2330
msgid "Exploration Priorities"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2332
msgid "Exploration ships always move"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2333
msgid ""
"toward the closest unexplored Deep Space System Marker. In case of a tie,"
" apply the following, in order:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2334
msgid ""
"• The ship moves toward the hex closest to a previously explored Deep "
"Space hex (this makes them more efficient in their exploration)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2335
msgid ""
"• The single Exploration ship exploring toward the human player chooses "
"the hex further from the Replicator Home System."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2336
msgid ""
"• The other two Exploration ships chooses the hex closer from the "
"Replicator Home System."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2344
msgid "Additional Exploration Ship Rules"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2346
msgid "• Exploration ships never join Fleets and always act independently."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2347
msgid ""
"• Exploration ships never enter a hex containing a human player ship. "
"Other than this, they ignore the presence of human player ships when "
"making movement decisions (in other words, they ignore Self-Preservation;"
" 7.8.3)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2348
msgid "• Exploration ships always retreat from combat as soon as possible."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2349
msgid ""
"• If all Exploration ships are eliminated and there are still unexplored "
"Deep Space hexes, the Replicators will create another Exploration ship in"
" the next Economic Phase. The new Exploration ship is produced at the "
"Full Replicator Colony closest to unexplored Deep Space. This is done "
"instead of the Hull that the Colony would have usually produced. Since "
"Exploration ships have a Hull Size of 2, this means that Colony "
"effectively produces 2 Hull Points instead of 1 during that Economic "
"Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2350
msgid ""
"• If all remaining unexplored Deep Space hexes can only be reached by the"
" Replicators by moving through the human player Home System, immediately "
"flip all remaining Deep Space System Markers to their explored sides."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2351
msgid ""
"• After Deep Space has been fully explored, all Exploration ships move to"
" the nearest Replicator Colony, where each ship is converted to 2 Hulls."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2352
msgid "To player HW"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2353
msgid "To Replicator HW"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2354
msgid ""
"EXAMPLE: Exploration ship A in hex C11 is the first ship to move into the"
" first row of Deep Space, so it becomes the ship that will explore toward"
" the human player Home System (7.5.1). Since both D11 and D12 are equally"
" valid, a die roll randomly determines which hex to explore (7.3.8). "
"Exploration ship B in hex B10 can explore either C9 or C10. Since C11 is "
"a Deep Space hex that has been successfully explored, it will choose C10 "
"(7.5.3). Ship B explores C10, finds an Asteroid, and enters the hex. Next"
" turn, ship B explores C9 and reveals a Barren Planet with Non-Player "
"Alien ships (not shown). Since it cannot enter hex C9, it will explore "
"D10 during the next Movement Phase. If it is able to enter hex D10, it "
"will explore D9 next because it is closer to the Replicator Home System "
"than E9 (7.5.3). If it can enter D9, it will explore C8 next because it "
"is closer to the Replicator Home System than D8, and so on."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2362
msgid "Replicator Movement"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2364
msgid ""
"• Note: Exploration ships are an exception to the rules in this section. "
"They have their own rules for movement and never join Fleets (7.5)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2365
msgid "• Replicator ships never enter Black Holes or Supernovas."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2366
msgid ""
"• Revealed Replicator ships always prefer to convert back into unrevealed"
" Hulls. They will always move into, or through, a Replicator Colony if "
"doing so will not require extra movement."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2367
msgid ""
"• At any time, if two hexes fulfill a movement priority equally, apply "
"the following:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2368
msgid ""
"- Replicator ships prioritize moving into a hex with unescorted non-"
"combat ships and destroying them."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2369
msgid "- They also prioritize moving into an Asteroid or Nebula."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2370
msgid ""
"• If multiple hexes are equally viable movement options, roll a die to "
"randomly determine the move."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2371
msgid "Space Empires: All Good Things - Solo/Coop Scenario Book Version 1.0 22"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2372
msgid ""
"• In addition to the above, Replicator Fleets have additional movement "
"rules covered in section [7.8]."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2380
msgid "During Home System Exploration"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2382
msgid "Until the Replicator"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2383
msgid ""
"Home System is fully explored, all ships follow these movement "
"priorities, in order:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2384
msgid ""
"• Move into the nearest unexplored Home System hex that can be reached "
"this turn and explore it during the Exploration Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2385
msgid ""
"- If it contains a Mineral, remove it, and add its value in CP to the "
"Replicator Production Sheet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2386
msgid "- If it contains a planet, it is immediately colonized (7.10)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2387
msgid ""
"• Move toward the nearest unexplored Home System hex, even if other ships"
" are also moving toward it."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2388 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2391
msgid ""
"PLAY NOTE: The Replicator AI does not have Exploration technology or "
"Exploration ships until after the Home System is completely explored "
"(7.4)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2399
msgid "Home System Fully Explored"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2401
msgid "After all Replicator Home"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2402
msgid ""
"System hexes have been explored, all Replicator ships (except Exploration"
" ships) will begin to form or join Fleets (7.7.1)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2410
msgid "Replicators Fleet Formation"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2412
msgid ""
"• Fleets are always represented by one of the five included Fleet "
"markers; use alternatives if more are needed. Unlike normal fleets (MRB "
"1.3), having more than one Replicator ship in a hex does NOT make it a "
"Fleet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2413
msgid ""
"• Replicator Fleets serve as groups of ships as usual, but also as "
"rallying points for all ships not yet in a Fleet to move toward. "
"Replicator ships/Hulls usually move toward Fleets (with some exceptions; "
"see [7.9])."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2414
msgid "• Fleets never split unless a Task requires it (7.9)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2415
msgid ""
"• Fleets will only combine in order to attack in concert on the same turn"
" (see priorities 1 and 2 of section [7.8.1])."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2423
msgid "Forming Fleets"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2425
msgid ""
"• Fleets begin to form after the Replicator Home System has been "
"completely explored. Replicator ships move toward the nearest Replicator "
"Fleet and join that Fleet upon entering its hex."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2426
msgid ""
"• If two or more Fleets are equidistant, the ships will move toward the "
"Fleet closest to the Replicator Home System. If a ship cannot reach a "
"Fleet during its turn, move within the limits of Self-Preservation "
"(7.8.3)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2427
msgid ""
"• For convenience, you may opt to remove ships that are in Fleets from "
"the map and place them on the Replicator Fleet card but note that the "
"Fleet card only has spaces for three of the five available Replicator "
"Fleet markers."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2435
msgid "The First Fleet"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2437
msgid "The first Replicator Fleet forms the"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2438
msgid ""
"moment the Replicator Home System is fully explored. Place a Fleet marker"
" in the hex containing the ship that is closest to"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2439
msgid ""
"the Exploration ship designated to explore toward the human player Home "
"System (7.5.1)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2440
msgid ""
"If there is still movement to be completed before the Economic Phase and "
"the first Fleet marker has not yet been placed, place the first Fleet in "
"the hex containing the ship that is closest to the Colony that will "
"produce the Exploration ship that will be chosen to explore toward the "
"human player."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2441
msgid ""
"The first Fleet will follow the above-noted Exploration ship until a "
"fully explored path to the human player Home System is created. During "
"each Movement Phase, the Exploration ship moves, and the Fleet then moves"
" into (or towards) the hex it previously occupied. After a fully explored"
" path is created, this Fleet will either attack through that path or "
"defend that path."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2449
msgid "Additional Fleets"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2451
msgid "All Replicator ships move toward/"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2452
msgid ""
"join the first Fleet until one of the following conditions causes another"
" Fleet to form (either of these conditions can occur more than once per "
"game):"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2453
msgid ""
"• Separate Explored Path to Human Space: A new Fleet forms when a "
"separate path to the human player Home System exists (ignore this "
"condition if a Superior human player Fleet is in the Replicator Home "
"System – Superiority is defined in section [7.8.2]). A separate path "
"meets all following criteria."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2454
msgid "- Is fully explored, and"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2455
msgid "- Reaches the human player Home System, and"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2456
msgid "- A Replicator ship is able to traverse it, and"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2457
msgid "- Does not come within four hexes of another Replicator Fleet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2458
msgid ""
"Example: A path that is five hexes away from the Replicator Fleet but "
"forces the Replicator ships to move into or through a hex containing Non-"
"Player Aliens or a Black Hole, is not a valid, separate, explored path."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2459
msgid ""
"• Human Player Ships Near Replicator Colony: A new Fleet forms when a "
"human player ship is closer to a Replicator Colony than any Replicator "
"Fleet, and no Fleet is within four hexes of the human player ship."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2460
msgid ""
"A new Fleet can form only when there are ships available that do not "
"already belong to a Fleet. Place a Fleet marker in the hex containing the"
" ship closest to either the separate explored path or the human player "
"ship that triggered the formation of the Fleet. For the “Human Player "
"Ships Near Replicator Colony” condition, place the Fleet marker in a hex "
"that is closer to the Replicator Home System than to the human player "
"ship if possible."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2461 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2465
msgid ""
"Designer Note: Similar to your fleets, each Replicator Fleet has a "
"purpose – whether to attack/defend or hunt down a ship in their space. "
"That purpose may change over time, but Fleet creation should be "
"considered with that purpose in mind."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2462
msgid "Space Empires: All Good Things - Solo/Coop Scenario Book Version 1.0 23"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2473
msgid "Replicators Fleet Movement"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2475
msgid ""
"After the first Fleet forms, the Replicators will follow the below steps "
"during each Movement Phase:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2476
msgid "1. Move all Exploration ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2477
msgid "2. Form additional Fleets as required (7.7.3)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2478
msgid "3. Move Fleets."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2479
msgid ""
"4. Move ships that do not belong to Fleets toward/into hexes containing "
"Fleet markers (7.7.1)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2487
msgid "Movement Priorities"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2489
msgid "Replicator Fleets move according"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2490
msgid ""
"to the following priorities, in order (see [7.8.2] for an explanation of "
"the terms Superior, Inferior, and Equal)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2491
msgid ""
"1. Attack a Colony. This turn, attack a human player Colony that is "
"undefended or defended by an Equal or Inferior Fleet. If more than one "
"Colony is eligible, attack the Equal or Inferior Colony with the most "
"Shipyards. If there are no Shipyards, attack the lowest level Colony."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2492
msgid ""
"2. Attack an Inferior Fleet. This turn, attack an Inferior human player "
"fleet (limited by Self-Preservation; 7.8.3). If more than one fleet is "
"eligible, attack the strongest fleet that is still Inferior."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2493
msgid ""
"3. Attack an Equal Fleet: This turn, attack an Equal human player fleet "
"if that fleet could attack a Replicator Colony on its turn."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2494
msgid ""
"4. Attack a Non-Player Alien Planet: This turn, attack an NPA planet with"
" a Replicator Fleet of 12 Hull Points or more, not counting PD, "
"Exploration, Scan, or SW ships (limited by Self-Preservation)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2495
msgid ""
"5. Move: Use an explored path to move toward/away from a human player "
"Colony or human player ships (limited by Self- Preservation). If a "
"Replicator Fleet has a choice between a human player colony or human "
"player ships, it will prioritize the human player ships if the Replicator"
" Fleet is closer to its own Home System than the Human Player Home "
"System. If there is more than one fleet or Colony to choose from, it will"
" move toward the closest one (limited by Self-Preservation.) If the "
"closest human fleet is Equal, the Replicator Fleet will attempt to move "
"around that fleet if it can move into the human player Home System this "
"turn. Otherwise, it will move adjacent to that human fleet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2496
msgid ""
"The above priorities mean that a Replicator Fleet will only move toward "
"the Replicator Home System because of Self- Preservation or to attack an "
"Inferior fleet that turn."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2497
msgid ""
"When considering the movement of Replicator Fleets and/or evaluating "
"fleet strength (7.8.2), always consider ALL the Replicator ships on the "
"board, regardless of whether they belong to a Fleet since merging "
"ships/fleets have the potential to change whether a human player fleet is"
" Superior/Equal/Inferior."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2498
msgid ""
"EXAMPLE: Two Replicator Fleets are both within range of a human player "
"planet guarded by a fleet. Although the human player fleet may be "
"Superior to each individual Replicator Fleet, the two Replicator Fleets "
"will combine for an attack if their combined strength makes the human "
"player fleet Inferior (see priority 1 above)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2506
msgid "Fleet Comparison"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2508
msgid "When comparing fleets that can attack"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2509
msgid ""
"each other, add up the total number of Hull Points on each side and apply"
" the following considerations:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2510
msgid "• Do not count non-combat ships or Exploration ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2511
msgid "• A human player base counts as double (i.e., 6 Hull Points)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2512
msgid "• Each Mine counts as 1.5 Hull Points (don’t round)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2513
msgid ""
"• <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Insectoids #43</span> and <span class"
"=\"text-uppercase\">Giant Race #34</span> ships are counted normally, but"
" never count for less than 1 Hull Point. For example, an Insectoid DD or "
"CA each count as 1 Hull Point."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2514
msgid ""
"If one side has 25% more Hull Points or greater, that side is Superior "
"and the other side is Inferior."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2515
msgid "If neither side has 25% more hulls, the sides are Equal."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2516
msgid ""
"EXAMPLE: The Replicators have three Type 0 ships (1 Hull Point each), an "
"Exploration ship (not counted/not ever part of a Fleet), and five Hulls, "
"totaling 8 Hull Points. The human player has two Mines (1.5 Hull Points "
"each) and two Cruisers (2 Hull Points each), totaling 7 Hull Points. "
"Since neither side has 25% more Hull Points, the fleets are Equal."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2517
#, python-format
msgid ""
"If the human player had one fewer Mine, they would have 5.5 Hull Points "
"and would be considered an Inferior fleet (8 - 5.5 = 2.5, and 2.5 is more"
" than 25% of 5.5)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2518
#, python-format
msgid ""
"If, instead, the human player had two more Mines (for 10 total Hull "
"Points), the Replicator Fleet would be Inferior (10 - 8 = 2, and 2 is 25%"
" of 8). In this case, due to the rule of Self- Preservation, the "
"Replicator Fleet would not attack, but it wouldn’t move away either, "
"because the human player’s Mines cannot attack – only the two Cruisers "
"can attack, and the Replicator Fleet is not Inferior to a fleet of two "
"Cruisers."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2526
msgid "Self-Preservation"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2528
msgid "Replicator movement priorities 2,"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2529
msgid ""
"4, and 5 are limited by Self-Preservation, meaning that the Replicators "
"will only follow those priorities when doing so will not cause them to be"
" attacked by a Superior human player fleet during the human player’s "
"turn. Generally, this means that Replicator Fleets will advance against "
"Colonies or fleets to which they are Equal or Superior and retreat out of"
" range from fleets to which they are Inferior."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2530
msgid "Space Empires: All Good Things - Solo/Coop Scenario Book Version 1.0 24"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2531
msgid ""
"Replicators always try to get as close as possible to human fleets and "
"the human player Home System without being defeated by a Superior human "
"player fleet. When ships are added to – or removed from – each side’s "
"fleets, it could cause the Replicators to switch between advancing and "
"retreating. Replicators will always consider possible merges of human "
"player fleets in their decisions (see examples below)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2532
msgid ""
"Replicator Fleets will not fall back beyond their Homeworld. If faced by "
"a Superior fleet in the Replicator Home System, Replicator Fleets will "
"retreat toward the Homeworld. They will stop on the Homeworld, even if a "
"Superior fleet could attack that turn."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2533
msgid ""
"The Replicators ignore the possibility of a Black Hole Slingshot (MRB "
"31.0) when applying the rule of Self-Preservation."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2541
msgid "Replicator Fleet Movement Examples"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2543
msgid "For the below"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2544
msgid ""
"examples, the human player has two Destroyers (2 Hull Points) in one hex "
"and three Destroyers (3 Hull Points) in an adjacent hex. The Replicators "
"have a Fleet of three Hulls that is two hexes away from both human "
"player-occupied hexes. No Colony can be attacked this turn (Priority 1), "
"so depending on other factors, the Replicators would do the following:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2545
msgid ""
"• If the Replicator Fleet can move two hexes this turn, it will attack "
"the two-Destroyer fleet (Priority 2). It will not attack the three-"
"Destroyer fleet because that fleet is not Inferior. The possibility that "
"the Replicator Fleet could sustain losses in the attack against the two-"
"Destroyer fleet – thus becoming Inferior to the three-Destroyer fleet "
"after the battle (thereby triggering Self-Preservation) – is not taken "
"into consideration."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2546
msgid ""
"• If the Replicator Fleet can move two hexes this turn AND there is one "
"more Replicator Hull that could also reach either hex containing the "
"human fleets, the single Hull will combine with the Replicator Fleet and "
"attack. At that point both human player fleets are Inferior, so the "
"Replicators will attack the three-Destroyer fleet (the strongest Inferior"
" fleet, Priority 2)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2547
msgid ""
"• If the Replicator Fleet can only move one hex this turn, it will not "
"move into any hex where both human fleets could attack it together. Five "
"Destroyers are Superior to three Hulls, and Priority 5 is limited by "
"Self-Preservation (meaning the Replicator Fleet will not move if doing so"
" opens them to attack by a Superior fleet)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2548
msgid ""
"• If the Replicators can only move one hex this turn, but the human "
"player can move two hexes, the Replicator Fleet will retreat, moving to a"
" hex that is at least three hexes away from one of the human player "
"fleets, because of Self-Preservation. This may cause the Replicator Fleet"
" to retreat toward the Replicator Home System. If an Asteroid hex was "
"adjacent to the Replicator Fleet and the human player was not able to "
"enter that hex this turn, the Replicator Fleet would enter the Asteroid "
"hex in order to stay as close as possible to the human player Home System"
" without being attacked by a Superior fleet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2549
msgid ""
"• If both the Replicators and the human player can move one hex this turn"
" and the encounter is near the human player Home System, the Replicator "
"Fleet will move to the hex closest to a human player Colony (Priority 5) "
"in which the Replicator Fleet could not be attacked by both human player "
"fleets together."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2557
msgid "Replicator Tasks"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2559
msgid ""
"Tasks are special assignments that supersede other Replicator ship/Fleet "
"movement rules."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2567
msgid "Gain Non-Player Alien RP"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2569
msgid "If the Replicators have not"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2570
msgid ""
"gained RP for encountering Non-Player Aliens, the Replicator ship in the "
"Replicator Home System closest to an NPA planet is assigned the Task to "
"earn that RP. This ship does not form or join a Fleet – instead it "
"attacks the nearest NPA planet. This ship’s movement is still limited by "
"Self-Preservation until it reaches the NPA planet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2578
msgid "Gain Human RP"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2580
msgid "If the normal movement rules will not"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2581
msgid ""
"result in an attack against the human player, but a Replicator ship is "
"capable of attacking human ships this turn – and that attack will earn "
"the Replicators at least one RP – then one Replicator ship is assigned to"
" make the attack, separating from a Fleet to do so if necessary."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2589
msgid "Colonize an Undefended Planet"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2591
msgid "If at any time there is an"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2592
msgid ""
"undefended and uncolonized planet, a Replicator ship is assigned to "
"colonize that planet, limited by Self-Preservation. If it can be "
"colonized during the same turn this Task was assigned, the assigned ship "
"will always colonize the planet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2600
msgid "Conquer a Non-Player Alien Planet"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2602
msgid "Under certain"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2603
msgid ""
"circumstances, the Replicators will form a Fleet to attack an NPA planet."
" Note that, whereas Priority 4 (7.8.1) can result in an existing "
"Replicator Fleet attacking an NPA planet as a target of opportunity, this"
" Task is different."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2604
msgid ""
"• This Task will only be assigned when playing on the Replicators Large "
"map (7.14)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2605
msgid ""
"• This Task will never be assigned if there is more than one human combat"
" ship outside of the human player Home System."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2606
msgid ""
"• This Task will not be assigned unless the NPA planet can be attacked by"
" Economic Phase 10. Note that the Replicators will still sometimes attack"
" NPA colonies after Economic Phase 10 because of Movement Priority 4, but"
" this will not occur because of this Task. After that point in the game, "
"the Replicators will attack eligible NPA planets if they are en route to "
"the human player Home System but will no longer go out of their way to "
"attack them."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2607
msgid ""
"• At the start of the Replicator turn, if there are 10 or more ships "
"(whether in a Fleet or not) that are either in the Replicator Home System"
" or within one hex of it and can attack a NPA planet before the next "
"Economic Phase, they will perform that attack."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2608
msgid "Space Empires: All Good Things - Solo/Coop Scenario Book Version 1.0 25"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2609
msgid ""
"• Place a Fleet marker on the target NPA planet. Move all eligible "
"Replicator ships toward the planet (but only those that can reach it "
"before the next Economic Phase). Ships that cannot make it in time should"
" be moved normally."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2610
msgid ""
"• The Replicators will delay their attack until they have the maximum "
"number of Hulls possible before the next Economic Phase. EXAMPLE: If the "
"Replicators will be able to attack with 12 Hulls on Turn 3, they will not"
" attack with 10 Hulls on Turn 2."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2620
msgid ""
"Whenever colonizing a planet, the Replicators always expend only one Hull"
" Point. If there are no available ships worth only one Hull Point, they "
"will convert a larger ship back to Hulls before colonizing."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2621 app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2624
msgid ""
"Designer Note: Making special rules for them to use single hull ships in "
"the vicinity or when to just colonize with a larger ship was not worth "
"the effort. This is much simpler."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2632
