#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2824
msgid "Conversion Example"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2826
msgid "The Replicators have 5 RP and"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2827
msgid ""
"are attacking. The Replicators have one SW, one PD, two Type II ships, "
"and 10 unrevealed Hulls. The human player has seven Mines, three "
"Fighters, one CV, and two DDs. There is a Raider within three hexes of "
"the battle."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2828
msgid ""
"The first two steps (7.11.1.1 & 7.11.1.2) are skipped because there are "
"no unescorted non-combat ships and no lone SD, DD, or Transport."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2829
msgid "Space Empires: All Good Things - Solo/Coop Scenario Book Version 1.0 27"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2830
msgid ""
"Following 7.11.1.3, they convert Hulls to Scan ships. The Replicators "
"have encountered Raiders before, and since there is a Raider within three"
" hexes of the battle, the third row of the table is used. They roll a 9, "
"so two Hulls convert to a Scan ship. Eight unrevealed Hulls remain."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2831
msgid ""
"For [7.11.1.4], Hulls are converted to Minesweepers. Since there are "
"Mines in the battle and the Replicators have encountered them before, the"
" last row of the table is used. They roll a 2, so the Replicators need to"
" have enough SW ships to clear half the Mines. They have Minesweeping 2 "
"technology because they have swept three Mines previously. Since one "
"Replicator SW is already present, converting one Hull to add one more SW "
"will allow them to clear four Mines. Seven unrevealed Hulls remain."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2832
msgid ""
"For [7.11.1.5], Hulls convert to PD ships. There are three Fighters in "
"the battle and the Replicators have encountered them previously, so the "
"fifth row of the table is used. They roll a 1, but there is already a PD "
"ship present, so no additional PD ships are added."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2833
msgid ""
"Finally, in [7.11.1.6], the seven remaining unrevealed Hulls are "
"converted to three Type V ships and one Type IV ship."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2834
msgid ""
"The resulting Fleet is made up of one Scan ship, two SWs, one PD, two "
"Type II ships, one Type IV ship, and three Type V ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2842
msgid "Attack Priorities"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2844
msgid "Replicator ships attack according to"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2845
msgid "the priorities below."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2846
msgid "• PD ships always fire at Fighters first."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2847
msgid "• Scan ships always fire at Raiders first."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2848
msgid "• All other Replicator ships prioritize enemy ships as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2849
msgid "- Ships with the smallest Hull Size, then"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2850
msgid "- Ships with the lowest Defense Strength, then"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2851
msgid "- Ships with the highest Attack Strength, then"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2852
msgid "- Ships that have not yet fired."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2862
msgid "The Replicators never screen their ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2863
msgid ""
"However, Replicator Scan ships and SW ships can only be fired upon if the"
" human player has more ships present than the Replicators. In any case, "
"Replicator Scan ships and SW ships can fire normally."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2871
msgid "Retreat"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2873
msgid "Replicator ships will retreat (when eligible) if"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2874
msgid ""
"the human player has three times as many Hull Points (or more) in the "
"battle. As noted in [7.8.2], a human player Base counts as double (6 Hull"
" Points)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2875
msgid "The Replicator Flagship will always retreat if it has taken 2 damage."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2883
msgid "Replicator Economic Phase"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2885
msgid ""
"Each Full Replicator Colony produces one Hull. No ship type is chosen at "
"the time of production. The Replicator can carry over more than 30 CP per"
" turn."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2893
msgid "Production/Development"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2895
msgid "The Replicators will produce"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2896
msgid "Hulls and develop technologies as indicated below (cost permitting)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2897
msgid ""
"In Economic Phases 1-3, the Replicators will buy one extra Hull at their "
"Homeworld for 8 CP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2898
msgid "Starting with Economic Phase 4 and thereafter:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2899
msgid ""
"• If they have the <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Fast Replicators "
"#60</span> Empire Advantage and have Move 5 technology or lower, buy the "
"next level of Move technology for 15 CP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2900
msgid ""
"• If they have the <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Advanced Research "
"#64</span> Replicators Empire Advantage, buy one RP for 25 CP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2901
msgid ""
"• If they have the <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Replicator Capitol "
"#65</span> Empire Advantage, buy one extra Hull for 8 CP and place it at "
"the Replicator Homeworld."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2902
msgid "• In all other cases, when 8 CP or more are available, roll a die:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2903
msgid ""
"- 1-4: Buy one extra Hull for 8 CP and place it at the Replicator "
"Homeworld."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2904
msgid ""
"- 5-8: Buy one RP for 30 CP (25 CP for <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Advanced Research #64</span> Replicators)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2905
msgid ""
"- 9-10: Buy next level of Move technology for 20 CP (15 CP for <span "
"class=\"text-uppercase\">Fast Replicators #60</span>)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2906
msgid ""
"• Otherwise, if Deep Space is fully explored, no Minerals remain on the "
"map, and the Replicators cannot make their required purchase, buy one "
"extra Hull for 8 CP and place it at the Replicator Homeworld."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2914
msgid "Replicators Standard"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2916
msgid ""
"A half-hex on the right edge sometimes needs to be in play to fit all 26 "
"Home System markers."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2917
msgid "Space Empires: All Good Things - Solo/Coop Scenario Book Version 1.0 28"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2925
msgid "Replicators Large"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2927
msgid "COOPERATIVE SCENARIOS"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:2928
msgid ""
"These scenarios were designed by an avid fan and playtester of Space "
"Empires to allow players to play against “the game” rather than each "
"other. These scenarios are ideal for teaching the original game and Close"
" Encounters to new players. They are also ideal for playing with "
"significant others that might not take too kindly to direct conflict."
msgstr ""

