#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4963
msgid "Space Empires: All Good Things - Solo/Coop Scenario Book Version 1.0 47"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4964
msgid ""
"• Morale: Morale is a statistic used to determine if the AP will begin "
"retreating ships from a battle. It is tracked using the morale counter "
"for a given AP side on the AP Bot PAC but it resets after every battle "
"round and is recalculated every time it is checked."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4965
msgid ""
"- Calculating Morale: Unlike Paranoia, Morale is re- calculated at the "
"start of every battle round, after checking for Fleet Size Bonus, if the "
"AP has any damaged or destroyed ships and it is after the first round. "
"Morale resets to 1 and then is modified based on the following (minimum "
"1):"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4966
msgid "▪ +1 per damaged AP ship"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4967
msgid "▪ -1 per damaged Player ship"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4968
msgid ""
"▪ +1 if the opposition has an un-countered Special Technology (i.e. has "
"FTR but AP lacks PD in this battle)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4969
msgid "▪ +1 if greater than half of AP’s ships are damaged or destroyed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4970
msgid "▪ +2 per destroyed AP ship"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4971
msgid "▪ +2 if the opposition has Fleet Size Bonus"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4972
msgid "▪ -2 if the AP has Fleet Size Bonus"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4973
msgid "▪ +2 if any friendly BCs are present."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4974
msgid ""
"▪ +3 if fighting a DS DM with at least one ineffective ship (e.g. "
"Fighters, Raiders, BDs)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4975
msgid ""
"- Raider Fleet Morale: AP Raiders make a special Morale check at the "
"start of any battle wherein they decide if they want to remain cloaked. "
"Remaining Cloaked does not count as a lost or won battle. This is skipped"
" if they are unable to cloak due to Scanner technology present. Calculate"
" Morale treating enemy unswept Mines and hull size 3 or greater ships as "
"destroyed AP ships. In subsequent combat rounds, the same adjustments "
"apply, and the AP makes a Morale check in every combat round regardless "
"of having any damaged or destroyed ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4976
msgid ""
"- Checking Morale: After calculating Morale, when the AP would first be "
"able to fire with a ship, roll 1d100. If equal to or less than the "
"corresponding 1d100 Morale value for the AP on the Paranoia/Morale Track,"
" the AP fails its Morale Check and will begin Retreating (see below). "
"Morale is no longer tested in this battle after the AP fails its Morale "
"Check. If it passes its Morale Check, the AP continues fighting and "
"Morale has to be Checked again in subsequent battle rounds."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4977
msgid ""
"- Example: The AP has 2 BCs fighting a Player’s 2 BBs and is using the BC"
" Hit and Run Strategy. One BC took damage in the first round. At the "
"start of round 2, neither side has Fleet Size Bonus. Morale is calculated"
" to be 5 (starting with 1 then, +1 damaged BC, +1 greater than half AP’s "
"ships are damaged/destroyed, +2 BCs are present). A d100 is rolled for "
"62. The AP passes and will not retreat. In round 2, the AP’s damaged BC "
"is destroyed and the other BC takes 1 damage. At the start of Round 3, "
"the Player has Fleet Size Bonus. Morale is calculated to be 9 (starting "
"at 1 then, +1 damaged BC, +2 BC destroyed, +1 greater than half AP’s "
"ships damaged/destroyed, +2 opposition has Fleet Size Bonus, +2 BCs are "
"present). A d100 is rolled for 71, the AP attempts to retreat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4978
msgid ""
"- Screening: The AP screens damaged ships or Transports if able, "
"preferring Transports and then Key Ships based on Strategy."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4979
msgid ""
"- Retreating: The AP attempts the safest possible retreat. When the AP is"
" Retreating, each ship will retreat instead of firing unless doing so "
"would expose a damaged ship that could otherwise be screened until "
"retreated. The AP retreats to an eligible retreat hex such that this "
"Fleet could potentially halt the advance of the enemy."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4980
msgid ""
"- Targeting: Each firing AP ship considers these targeting priorities in "
"order."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4981
msgid ""
"- Technology: The marking of seen technology occurs after the battle is "
"over."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4982
msgid ""
"1. Prevent Transport landing: Target units carrying ground forces capable"
" of landing on a friendly planet, if present and able."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4983
msgid "2. Prevent Boarding: Target BDs if present and able."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4984
msgid ""
"3. Destroy Special: If the enemy has a ship for which the AP has a "
"Special Counter Technology, it will have the appropriate ship target the "
"relevant enemy ship."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4985
msgid ""
"4. Prevent Fleet Size Bonus: If enemy has or is 1 ship away from "
"obtaining Fleet Size Bonus, target the ship with the smallest hull that "
"is easiest to hit."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4986
msgid ""
"5. Focus Fire: Target the most damaged ship, then smallest ship then ship"
" with lowest overall defense, then ship with highest overall attack, then"
" ship with highest experience (or Crew Card), then the ship with the "
"highest movement (including Fast), then ship with highest Tactics. "
"Otherwise randomly select or use the Prime Directive."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:4987
msgid "Space Empires: All Good Things - Solo/Coop Scenario Book Version 1.0 48"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5015
msgid "After Winning at Colonies"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5017
msgid ""
"• If “Off Camera” NPA Battles was not used: when an AP Fleet wins space "
"combat above a colony and ground combat was lost or did not occur, the AP"
" purchases a Colony Ship and places it in the nearest FOB (or HW) in the "
"next EP. This is cancelled if Terraforming 1 is not researched. "
"Destination Checks for this Colony Ship are always to take the fastest "
"and safest route to the closest uncolonized friendly planet taking Threat"
" and terrain into account. If this Colony Ship is destroyed and the un-"
"colonized planet remains, a new one is purchased, and colonization is re-"
"attempted."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5018
msgid ""
"• If ground combat was lost or did not occur, the Expansion Fleet will "
"bombard the planet down to zero instead of making Destination Checks. "
"Once the colony is eliminated, a Colony Ship will be purchased as above."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5019
msgid ""
"• If ground combat was won and this is a Player planet, the AP gains "
"technology as per the normal ground combat rules. It can mark all "
"relevant technologies as “seen”."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5020
msgid "• All ground troops present remain stationed at this colony indefinitely."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5021
msgid ""
"• If the fleet taking this colony was an Expansion Fleet and it still "
"contains greater than 60 CP of ships, it will continue acting as an "
"Expansion Fleet. Otherwise, it becomes a Guard Fleet (13.29)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5022
msgid ""
"• The AP is eligible to draw Alien Technology cards as a Player (if in "
"use) but only draws 1 and it stays face-down until the next encounter "
"with a Player."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5023
msgid "Optional Rules"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5031
msgid "Hidden AP HS"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5033
msgid ""
"• Instead of revealing AP HS hexes when the AP makes its first Econ roll,"
" leave these hexes face down until the first time a Player unit enters "
"the AP HS. Then reveal and place colonies as described above under AP "
"Setup. If this is used, EVs drop off DS Minerals/Space Wrecks at the "
"nearest face down AP HS marker as if it were a colony. Nebula Miners are "
"functional but set aside with location unknown until AP HS is face-up."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5041
msgid "Alternative Quick Start"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5043
msgid ""
"Unlike the Quick Start variant from the base game, this variant starts "
"the Players as if they had had an average first 4 Econ Phases and "
"approximates how the AP Bot starts. All Players must resolve their quick "
"start before the AP bot. Players resolve Quick Start in turn order."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5044
msgid "1. Reveal all Player HS markers. Remove Minerals."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5045
msgid ""
"2. Place colony markers on all non-Barren colonies. Set all colonies to 5"
" CP side except for the three farthest from the HW which are on the 1 CP "
"side."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5046
msgid "3. Place an additional 1 SY on any colony."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5047
msgid "4. Place 5 MS Pipelines anywhere in Player HS, excluding the black hole."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5048
msgid ""
"5. Place starting units as normal except remove all colony ships. The "
"SCs, Miner and Flagship may be moved to any non-Black Hole hex."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5049
msgid ""
"6. Spend up to 100 CP on Technology. No more than 4 levels of a given "
"technology may be purchased. If 10 or fewer CP remain, they may be added "
"to the Carry Over from Last Turn entry."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5050
msgid ""
"7. Spend up to 20 CP on units (this includes combat and non- combat "
"capable ships as well as bases and ship yards). They may be placed in any"
" colony containing a SY, regardless of ship building capacity. If SYs "
"were built using the above CP, they may be placed on any colony. All "
"units placed have the latest technology equipped as appropriate. If fewer"
" than 6 CP remain, they may be added to the Carry Over from Last Turn "
"Entry."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5051
msgid ""
"8. Start the game but it is the beginning of Econ Phase 5 which may also "
"initiate a number of AP bot actions (13.24)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5059
msgid "AP Empire Advantage Cards"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5061
msgid ""
"• Their use is optional. They are kept facedown until the first AP "
"Unknown Fleet Generation. Using these cards may lead to an unbalanced, "
"but flavorful and thematic game. Many Empire Advantage cards can be used "
"as written and if no ruling is given below, they are to be used as "
"written. It may be that the AP’s behavior prior to revelation of their "
"Empire Advantage does not align with their Empire Advantage, that was "
"just an incredible deception on the part of the AP. No retroactive "
"consistency effects (apart from suggestions below) need be applied. It is"
" impossible to give tactical advice for the AP Bot for every permutation "
"of cards thus a game including these will rely on the Prime Directive. "
"Special Rules and rulings for specific cards are below. Some rulings may "
"replace normal card effects."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5062
msgid ""
"• Deal the AP Bot one Empire Advantage card, face down. This will be "
"revealed when an Unknown AP Fleet is first generated. Since these cards "
"are not revealed until the AP is encountered, some effects are applied "
"retroactively. The AP’s behavior prior to this reveal may have been "
"incongruent with the card, that is fine, they were just being deceptive."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5063
msgid ""
"• The AP will not select a strategy if it is fundamentally incompatible "
"with their revealed Empire Advantage (e.g. Fighters for Insectoid, "
"Raiders for <span class=\"text-uppercase\">House of Speed #53</span>)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5064
msgid ""
"• (#33) <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Celestial Knights #33</span>: If "
"the AP may charge and passed or did not have a Morale check, they will "
"charge. Having charged modifies their next Moracle check by +2."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5065
msgid ""
"• (#34) <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Giant Race #34</span>: The AP’s "
"FOB cost 40 CP instead and double the number of active fleets for "
"maintenance calculation purposes and fleet launch decisions."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5066
msgid "Space Empires: All Good Things - Solo/Coop Scenario Book Version 1.0 49"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5067
msgid ""
"• (#35) <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Industrious Race #35</span>: When "
"revealed, if AP has Terraforming, place colonies on all HS Asteroids. "
"These count as DS colonies. The AP will attempt to colonize DS Asteroids "
"as an NPA planet if any DS Asteroids exist within 2 rows of AP HS or a DS"
" colony."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5068
msgid ""
"• (#36) <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Ancient Race #36</span>: When "
"revealed, make 2 HS rolls."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5069
msgid ""
"• (#37) <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Space Pilgrims #37</span>: Fleets "
"can attack into black holes."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5070
msgid ""
"• (#38): <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Hive Mind #38</span>: Modify "
"Morale by -1 starting in round 2 of combat, by -2 starting in round 4 of "
"combat, by -3 starting in round 6 of combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5071
msgid ""
"• (#39): <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Nano-technology #39</span>: When "
"revealed, the AP receives 2 Space Wreck rolls."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5072
msgid ""
"• (#43): <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Insectoids #43</span>: Half the "
"number of active fleets (round down) for maintenance. This is applied "
"before the effect of any other maintenance reducing card."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5073
msgid ""
"• (#44): <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Immortals #44</span>: When "
"revealed, subtract 12 CP from the higher of Fleet or Tech. Use ability if"
" would prevent Morale increase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5074
msgid ""
"• (#45): <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Expert Tacticians #45</span>: Use"
" this definition for Fleet Size Bonus in Morale calculations."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5075
msgid ""
"• (46): Horseman of the Plains: Can retreat all immediately after morale "
"failure."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5076
msgid ""
"• (#48): <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Amazing Diplomats #48</span>: "
"Ignore the fact that this could be revealed after the AP has already "
"fought an NPA colony."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5077
msgid ""
"• (#49) <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Traders #49</span>: Instead gain "
"+1 DS rolls permanently."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5078
msgid ""
"• (#50): <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Cloaking Geniuses #50</span>: Can"
" buy SCT on fleet generation. Buy DD or SC with remainder Fleet CP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5079
msgid ""
"• (#52) <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Power to the People #52</span>: "
"EVs gain the benefit of this card."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5080
msgid ""
"• (#54) <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Powerful Psychics #54</span>: "
"Refund the AP 15 CP to Tech budget for Exploration 1. Use Prime Directive"
" when making decisions about Player units that are face up due to this "
"advantage."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5081
msgid ""
"• (#55) <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Shape Shifters #55</span>: If "
"Decoy shell game is used by an AP Extermination Fleet, generate all "
"fleets as normal then resolve the first hits as per <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Shape Shifters #55</span> Decoys in battle. When this is "
"triggered, then determine if this entire fleet was a decoy fleet. If so, "
"refund the AP the Fleet allotment, however, the AP retains knowledge of "
"what was encountered in the <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Shape Shifters"
" #55</span> decoy battle."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5082
msgid ""
"• (#58) <span class=\"text-uppercase\">On the Move #58</span>: Treat EVs "
"as non-combat ships with stats of a Base. All other behaviors unchanged "
"and they are not counted as Fleets. They are still ignored by DS DMs."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5083
msgid ""
"• (#187) <span class=\"text-uppercase\">War Sun #187</span>: After "
"revealed, AP Fleets gain Supernova move ability. The TN is placed on the "
"HW as soon as this card is revealed. It acts as a separate Extermination "
"Fleet that is always known and has no CP allotment, but it cannot leave"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5084
msgid ""
"the HS until Ship Size 6 is researched. It will remain at the HW, not "
"counting for maintenance, until then."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5085
msgid ""
"• (#190) <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Robotic Race #190</span>: Counts "
"as a permanent -1 to maintenance as seen with other sources of half "
"maintenance."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5086
msgid ""
"• (#191) <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Masters of the Gates #191</span>:"
" AP will use <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Warp Gates #63</span> to move"
" friendly Fleets on Offense into combat together."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5094
msgid "Misc Optional Rules"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5096
msgid ""
"• AP as Alternate Empire: The AP can play as the Alternate Empire. This "
"alters some Strategy as well as Ship/Tech purchasing above."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5097
msgid ""
"• Variable but Balanced Home System: Can be used but the AP still does "
"not need to explore its own HS. It will affect the AP’s ability to mine "
"Nebula. The 10 CP planets do not alter HS rolls but instead pull double "
"duty, counting as an extra DS roll, each. If lost, the HS penalties apply"
" as normal, and the DS roll is also lost."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5098
msgid ""
"• Facilities: The AP does not use Facilities. If the players use "
"Facilities, the AP gets extra HS Rolls to start (see [13.14])."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5099
msgid "• Scenario Cards:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5100
msgid "- Many can be used as written with some specific rulings below."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5101
msgid ""
"- <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Worth the Effort #113</span>: On every "
"EP that’s a multiple of 5 (i.e. 5, 10, 15), the AP gets a bonus DS roll "
"for barren planet colonies."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5102
msgid ""
"- <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Better Homes #122</span>: The AP gets an"
" extra HS roll at full strength."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5103
msgid ""
"• <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Warp Gates #63</span>: If the AP, "
"through game effects, has ships with <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Warp "
"Gates #63</span> it will use them as described in the <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Masters of the Gates #191</span> ruling above."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5104
msgid "• Tiles: The larger tile counters from Replicators may be used as desired."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5105
msgid ""
"• Amoebas: EVs act as Science Vessels. Science technology is purchased by"
" the AP automatically after Exploration 1 is researched without having "
"lost a ship to Amoebas. EVs are automatically upgraded. Once upgraded, "
"EVs stop Exploration and Mining mode and move to and research Amoebas per"
" scenario rules until all types have been researched. Once an Amoeba type"
" is researched, the AP targets Amoebas as if they were Player ships. "
"Strategy selection for some is dictated by Amoeba type and the AP will "
"auto-fail its Paranoia Check if needed to switch strategies."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5106
msgid ""
"• Advanced Construction: The AP ignores the requirement to have built an "
"SS4+ ship and only needs SS4 tech researched as a prerequisite for AC1."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5107
msgid "Space Empires: All Good Things - Solo/Coop Scenario Book Version 1.0 50"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5108
msgid ""
"• Space Pirates: If revealed by AP Exploration Technology, flip face up. "
"Then, after all movement has resolved for this turn, roll 1d10. On a 1-8,"
" the AP Hires the Pirate. Purchase from higher of Tech/Fleet Budget. On a"
" 9-10 or unable to hire, the Pirate is removed from play (Maybe he had a "
"bounty on his head and couldn’t stay.). If the AP Hired the Pirate, "
"immediately move this counter to the nearest non-Raider AP Fleet that is "
"not engaged in a battle. This Pirate is now part of and moves with this "
"AP Fleet. If Raider Strategy becomes active or no Fleets available, "
"immediately move this Pirate to the nearest friendly colony (even if a "
"battle just started). It will remain there until Raider Strategy is no "
"longer active and an eligible Fleet is present to join, in which case it "
"will again immediately join the nearest non-Raider Fleet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5109
msgid ""
"• AP Unique ships: The AP’s EVs are effectively a special unique ship "
"that does not change during the course of the game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5117
msgid "Alien Technology Cards"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5119
msgid ""
"• If used, these are gained by the AP the same was a Player would gain "
"them, except only 1 is drawn and it is kept face down until the next "
"Unknown AP Fleet is revealed. Scripting Strategies for all AP cards (or "
"multiple AP cards) is not possible or practical. Use the Prime Directive "
"if the AP would purchase inefficient units/technology for cards that "
"Players know about. If not using NPAs (not recommended), the AP pays for "
"Alien Technology cards out of the Fleet if able. Special rulings are "
"below:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5120
msgid ""
"• Reduce HS Maintenance penalty by 1 for every source of maintenance "
"reduction (including other card types) so long as the ship type appears "
"in the current AP Strategy. AP pays normal maintenance if first fleet "
"generation has not yet occurred."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5121
msgid "• Most Alien Technology cards can be used as written. Special Rulings:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5122
msgid ""
"• (#22) <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Omega Crystal #22</span>: The AP "
"may use the <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Omega Crystal #22</span>, if "
"able. If the majority of Key Ships (per Strategy) in a group misses or if"
" sufficient Key Ships was just lost that would raise Paranoia, it will "
"use the <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Omega Crystal #22</span>."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5123
msgid ""
"• (#27) <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Stealth Field Emitter #27</span>: "
"This Fleet becomes Unknown again. Convert the cost of current ships back "
"into allotted CP. If revealed again, no new Tech purchasing occurs during"
" Fleet generation. If <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Stealth Field "
"Emitter #27</span> is drawn by a Player for use against the AP, we "
"recommend discarding and drawing again."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5124
msgid ""
"• (#56) <span class=\"text-uppercase\">On Board Workshop #56</span>: AP "
"will use if using Fighter Strategy and a Known Fleet has less than "
"capacity Fighters present. Spend from Fleet budget. All Fighters auto-"
"refit if possible, spending from Fleet budget."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5125
msgid ""
"• (#57) <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Superhighway #57</span>: When "
"revealed, instead the AP gains +1 Movement technology for free."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5133
msgid "Resource Cards"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5135
msgid ""
"• Using Resource Cards may require use of the Prime Directive more than "
"other rules. If used, the AP draws Resource Cards at the same time as "
"Players but these are all kept in a face-down pile, and are flipped face "
"up when certain events occur. Face- up cards are eligible for play, but "
"does not necessarily mean the AP will play it immediately."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5136
msgid "• Flip 1 resource card face up at the:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5137
msgid "- End of the AP’s Econ Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5138
msgid "- Start of a battle, after ships are revealed/generated."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5139
msgid ""
"• When the text of a face-up resource card indicates it can be played in "
"this moment, roll 1d10. On a 1-8, the AP plays this card. If playing the "
"card requires discard of another card, discard from among the face-down "
"Resource Cards. Otherwise, skip playing this card."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5140
msgid ""
"• If there are face-up Resource Cards at the start of the AP’s Econ "
"Phase, make a Paranoia Check. On a Fail, the AP discards a random face-up"
" Resource Card for its listed CP value. The value is assigned to budget "
"as per DS roll. Regardless of any discards, flip face-down one random "
"remaining face- up Resource card and shuffle it back in with the face-"
"down Resource cards."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5141
msgid ""
"- Mission Cards: The AP cannot play Mission Cards for their effect. If "
"attempting to discard a Resource Card for CP value, the AP selects face "
"up Mission cards first."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5142
msgid ""
"- If the AP is the target of a Mission Card, instead of resolving the "
"card’s effect, make a Paranoia Check. On a Pass, the AP was immediately "
"able to complete the mission and gains a temporary +1 DS Roll in the next"
" Econ Phase. On a Fail, the AP was unable to complete the mission and "
"temporarily gets 1 less HS roll in the subsequent Econ Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5150
msgid "Crew Experience"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5152
msgid ""
"• Known AP Fleets track experience by ship as Players would. All ships in"
" an Unknown AP Fleet will have Green experience if they are generated in "
"the turn they are launched. Otherwise, they will be Skilled. If using Off"
" Camera NPA battles, Unknown AP Fleets may gain experience which will "
"affect all generated ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5153
msgid ""
"• Military academy: Works as for Players. If using Off Camera NPA "
"battles, promotion occurs on a 1-2 die result instead."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5161
msgid "Crew Cards"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5163
msgid ""
"• The AP draws Crew Cards at the same time as Players but they are kept "
"in a face-down pile without discarding. When the AP encounters NPAs "
"(unless Off Camera NPA Battles is used) or a Player, turn up to two Crew "
"Cards face-up. These are eligible Crew."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5164
msgid "Space Empires: All Good Things - Solo/Coop Scenario Book Version 1.0 51"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5165
msgid ""
"• If, after Fleet generation, any eligible Crew may be assigned to a ship"
" in this Fleet, assign it immediately. If multiple eligible Crew are "
"available, select the Crew that would be most appropriate for this "
"Fleet’s Strategy, considering Key Ships. Otherwise select randomly. "
"Assign the crew to the group that would best fit the crew’s abilities. "
"The other crew card is discarded. If no eligible Crew can be assigned, "
"shuffle both of these Crew cards back into the deck and the AP draws 1 "
"Crew card to its face-down pile of crew cards. Most crew cards can "
"function as written. Some Crew Cards require use of the Prime Directive. "
"Some Crew Cards may alter what the AP should consider to be Detrimental "
"Terrain."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5166
msgid ""
"• If a Crew Card reduces maintenance and the number of hull points in "
"this group is 5 or more, this crew instead provides -1 Maintenance in the"
" AP’s Econ Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5167
msgid ""
"• (#272) <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Patrol Leader #272</span>: If "
"assigned to a DD, instead, the AP gains +1 DS roll which is lost if this "
"Crew is eliminated or becomes not assigned to a DD."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5175
msgid "DS Planet Attributes"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5177
msgid ""
"• <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Dilithium Crystal #p4</span>: When this "
"colony becomes full, the AP will purchase a Transport at the nearest "
"HW/FOB. This Transport moves Dilithium crystal counters from this colony "
"to the AP HW along the fastest and safest route possible avoiding "
"Threatened hexes. When dropped off the AP gains a temporary +1 DS roll. "
"If the colony is ever blockaded or eliminated, the Transport remains "
"stationary at the nearest FOB/HW."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5178
msgid ""
"• <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Telepathic #p26</span>: The counter "
"affects the entire AP Fleet. Only one Fleet may benefit from this at any "
"given time."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5179
msgid ""
"• <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Abundant #p5</span>: On every EP that’s "
"a multiple of 5 (i.e. 5, 10, 15), the AP gets a bonus DS roll for this "
"colony."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5180
msgid ""
"• <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Wealthy #p6</span>: On every EP that’s a"
" multiple of 10 (i.e. 10, 20), the AP gets a bonus DS roll for this "
"colony."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5181
msgid ""
"• <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Poor #p7</span>: On every EP that’s a "
"multiple of 10 (i.e. 10, 20), the AP does not get a DS roll for this "
"colony."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5182
msgid ""
"• <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Desolate #p8</span>: The AP only gets a "
"DS roll for this colony on EPs that are multiples of 10 (i.e. 10, 20)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5183
msgid ""
"• <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Doomed #p13</span>: The AP will avoid "
"wasting resources colonizing this planet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5184
msgid ""
"• <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Builder #p14</span>: If the AP would "
"place an FOB, it will place one here (if not yet built), for free."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5185
msgid ""
"• <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Spaceport #p15</span>: If the AP has an "
"unknown fleet here during the EP, roll 1d10. On a 1-8, it will spend 8 CP"
" from the Fleet or Tech budget to add 6 CP to this unknown fleet’s "
"allocation. On a 9-10, nothing happens."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5193
msgid "AP in games against Replicators"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5195
msgid "• The AP will always reroll “Yarr!” strategy."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5196
msgid "• Do not use the Alternative Quick Start rule."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5197
msgid "• Do not use the Galactic Capitol."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5198
msgid ""
"• The AP adds 10 CP to Fleet Budget at game start. The AP will treat the "
"Max Terraforming and Goal DS planets as if the map was one size category "
"smaller (shift up one on the table)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/solo_scenario_book.py:5199
msgid ""
"• Some Tech and Fleet buying is different for the AP against Replicators "
"(see [13.37])."
msgstr ""

